This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning techniques to predict the quality of news headlines. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to analyze website logs, which makes cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely sub-category. The proposed deep learning model also involves techniques from machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with the issue of online user engagement, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.CY (Computers and Society).
